            "body": "Yeah that would've worked but wasn't my problem exactly.\r\nI figured out eventually that apparently I was calling a non-static method statically, so I changed \r\n` $callbackEvent = function(WhatsAppEventListener $listener) use ($phone, $from, $msgid, $type, $time, $name, $message) {\r\n            $listener->onGetMessage($phone, $from, $msgid, $type, $time, $name, $message);\r\n        };\r\n        $this->fireCallback($callbackEvent); ` \r\n\r\nin WhatsAppEvent.php to\r\n\r\n` global $variable;\r\n call_user_func_array(array($variable, \"onMessage\"), array($phone, $from, $msgid, $type, $time, $name, $message)); `\r\n\r\nand then suddenly it worked! Thanks for your effort anyway.",
